cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.NE 

The paper focuses on quantizing recurrent neural networks for efficient deployment on portable devices and servers. This topic falls under the broad category of machine learning and optimization, which is covered by cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also applies the proposed method to image classification tasks, which suggests a potential connection to computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper involves optimization techniques and neural network architectures, which are relevant to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-categories.
